NOTE ON SCENARIO DATA:

This MIT license covers the framework code (lib/, app/, scripts/, public/dlc/manifest.json,
etc.) and the original scenarios authored by the project contributors (located in
public/dlc/*.json that are tracked by git).

Scenarios that are derivative works of third-party intellectual property (such as the
Tang Twin Dragons series by Huang Yi, or Games Workshop's Warhammer 40,000 universe)
are NOT included in this repository. They live in the project author's private
development tree only, are listed in .gitignore, and are not redistributed under this
license. Trademarks, character names, and worldbuilding elements of those works remain
the property of their respective rights holders.

If you want to play with derivative scenarios, you must author your own data file
conforming to the scenario JSON schema (see DOCS in the repository or examples in the
included original scenarios) and place it under public/dlc/ yourself.
